      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BULA (1) flew the lids from the middle with a sensational turn of foot before finishing second (19.68) and beaten 0.8 lengths over 350m at this track. Hard to knock his form from this box, unbeaten in five starts. Must come into calculations. GOT FLAIR (3) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at Warragul behind My Gracie (23.18) in a Rank Limit - Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Expected to feature again. HERBIE (8) stalked the lead from a middle draw and boxed on well to finish 4.5 lengths back in third (23.26) at Warragul in a Rank Limit - Grade 5 over 400m. Has performed well from this box with a win and two minor placings to his name from four starts. Expected to be in this for a long way. SUMMER KOBIE (7) cannot be left out after placing as public elect last start.",
